toPairs

public static <U,V> Collection<Pair<U,V>> toPairs(Collection<? extends U> firstObjects,
                                                  V secondObject)
Creates pairs by "pairing-up" each object in a collection with the same partner object.

Type Parameters:
U - the type of the first object in the pair
V - the type of the second object in the pair
Parameters:
firstObjects - the objects to become the first objects in the pairs
secondObject - the object to be paired with all the firstObjects
Returns:
a collection of pairs containing an entry in firstObjects and secondObject
See Also:
toPairs(Class, Collection, Object)

toPairs

public static <T extends Pair<U,V>,U,V> Collection<T> toPairs(Class<T> pairClass,
                                                              Collection<? extends U> firstObjects,
                                                              V secondObject)
Creates pairs of the given pair subclass by "pairing-up" each object in a collection with the same partner object.

Expects the subclass to have a two-argument constructor, taking the first and second objects as arguments. The constructor does not need to be visible.

Type Parameters:
T - the type of the pair subclass to be returned
U - the type of the first object in the pair
V - the type of the second object in the pair
Parameters:
firstObjects - the objects to become the first objects in the pairs
secondObject - the object to be paired with all the firstObjects
Returns:
a collection of pairs containing an entry in firstObjects and secondObject
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if pairClass is null or if the given subclass cannot be instantiated using the expected two-argument constructor
See Also:
toPairs(Collection, Object)

                                     V secondObject)
Creates a pair.
